## Slide Layouts (14 types in master template)
1. **COVER** ŌĆö Full-bleed Higgsfield image, logo top-left, title centred, classification banner
2. **SECTION DIVIDER** ŌĆö Warm orange, day/chapter number in display font, subtitle
3. **CONTENT** ŌĆö Title + body (text, bullets, or image right)
4. **TWO COLUMN** ŌĆö Equal split or 60/40 (text left, visual right)
5. **FULL-BLEED IMAGE** ŌĆö Higgsfield behind text, dark overlay for legibility
6. **TABLE** ŌĆö Data table with header row in cyan, alternating row shading
7. **CHART PLACEHOLDER** ŌĆö Grey box with chart type label and caption
8. **QUOTE / KEY STAT** ŌĆö Large display number or pull-quote, minimal surrounding content
9. **MAP / GRAPHIC** ŌĆö Full-bleed graphic with annotation overlays
10. **ORBAT** ŌĆö Order of Battle layout, two forces, symbolic notation
11. **TIMELINE** ŌĆö Horizontal event line with date nodes and descriptions
12. **COMPARISON** ŌĆö Side-by-side platform or system comparison grid
13. **SUMMARY** ŌĆö Lesson summary ŌĆö 3ŌĆō5 key takeaways as numbered cards
14. **INSTRUCTOR NOTE** ŌĆö Dark amber border, "INSTRUCTOR NOTE" stamp, teaching guidance

## Higgsfield Image Prompts
Every prompt must include:
```
Style: cinematic military documentary, desaturated, [warm/cool] grading
Subject: [specific subject with operational context]
Mood: tense / professional / operational
Aspect: 16:9
Negative: cartoon, low quality, watermark, civilian aesthetic, cheerful, text
```

**Warm mode** (chapter dividers, strike content): `golden hour, orange atmospheric haze`
**Cool mode** (ISR, sensors, data): `night ops, blue-tinted NVG aesthetic, FLIR colouration`

## Classification Banner (all slides)
Bottom footer on every slide:
```
UNCLASSIFIED // SPECTRAL PCM ŌĆö FOR OFFICIAL TRAINING USE ONLY
```
Font: Courier New 10pt, colour `#9CA3AF`, left-aligned in footer zone.

## Anti-Patterns
- Never use white or light backgrounds
- Never use decorative accent lines under titles (AI slop tell)
- Never use cream/beige backgrounds
- Never centre body text (left-align prose and lists)
- Never use the same layout more than twice in a row
- All numeric data must be in Courier New ŌĆö no exceptions
- Never put text directly over a Higgsfield image without a dark overlay (min 40% opacity)
